What's all this noise about?

76
00:04:06,230 --> 00:04:06,930
Your Highness.

77
00:04:06,930 --> 00:04:08,570
These commoners have come to the wrong place,

78
00:04:08,570 --> 00:04:10,090
They've brought their complaint to the prince's mansion.

79
00:04:10,090 --> 00:04:11,820
I'll chase them away right now.

80
00:04:12,810 --> 00:04:15,340
Your Highness, please uphold justice for us!

81
00:04:22,570 --> 00:04:23,610
Bastard!

82
00:04:27,290 --> 00:04:28,130
Please get up.

83
00:04:28,650 --> 00:04:29,170
Come on.

84
00:04:29,170 --> 00:04:29,970
Please get up.

85
00:04:31,970 --> 00:04:32,530
You...

86
00:04:32,530 --> 00:04:33,320
go back now.

87
00:04:33,850 --> 00:04:34,490
I

88
00:04:34,490 --> 00:04:36,220
will make sure you get justice.

89
00:04:37,450 --> 00:04:38,909
Thank you, Your Highness.

90
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:39,840
Thank you, Your Highness.

91
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,050
Dad, now we have hope.

92
00:04:41,050 --> 00:04:41,580
Let's go.

93
00:04:42,159 --> 00:04:43,620
Thank you, Your Highness.

94
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:45,290
Prince is such a good person.

95
00:04:45,290 --> 00:04:46,570
Prince really cares about the people.

96
00:04:46,570 --> 00:04:47,200
Let's go.

97
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:47,890
Let's go.

98
00:04:47,890 --> 00:04:48,690
Let's go home.

99
00:04:51,610 --> 00:04:52,880
Now we have hope.

100
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:54,140
We can go home now, Dad.

101
00:04:56,850 --> 00:04:57,650
Beat them!

102
00:04:57,650 --> 00:04:58,710
What are you doing?

103
00:05:03,990 --> 00:05:04,920
Don't hit my dad!

104
00:05:06,850 --> 00:05:08,040
Don't hit my dad!

105
00:05:13,610 --> 00:05:15,330
My dad was old and weak.

106
00:05:17,930 --> 00:05:18,800
Before he

107
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:21,840
managed to return to the village, he...

108
00:05:25,810 --> 00:05:26,690
Later on,

109
00:05:28,450 --> 00:05:30,510
all the people in our stronghold became bandits.

110
00:05:30,510 --> 00:05:33,159
In this way, we managed to survive.

111
00:05:36,090 --> 00:05:37,210
Not long ago,

112
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:40,020
Prince Ying went out on an outing.

113
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:42,550
I had planned to take this opportunity

114
00:05:42,850 --> 00:05:44,360
to avenge my dad.

115
00:05:45,290 --> 00:05:47,000
However, he had already taken precautions

116
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,000
and stationed soldiers in advance.

117
00:05:49,610 --> 00:05:50,409
No way.

118
00:05:50,930 --> 00:05:51,770
Uncle Ying...

119
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:54,210
is humble and thrifty.

120
00:05:54,490 --> 00:05:56,350
How could he tolerate wicked servants

121
00:05:56,350 --> 00:05:57,860
harming others' lives?

122
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:00,290
He is your Uncle Ying.

123
00:06:01,970 --> 00:06:03,770
Of course you would speak up for him.

124
00:06:03,770 --> 00:06:04,650
No.

125
00:06:05,690 --> 00:06:06,490
If...

126
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,650
he were truly as you described,

127
00:06:08,850 --> 00:06:09,520
I will...

128
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:12,730
What will you do?

129
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:15,700
I'll scold him for you!

130
00:06:22,170 --> 00:06:22,960
Okay!

131
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:24,760
Scold him for me, then.

132
00:06:41,370 --> 00:06:43,050
If what he said is true,

133
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:46,850
it seems that he's not an unforgivable criminal.

134
00:06:49,409 --> 00:06:50,840
[Prince Ying's Mansion]

135
00:06:55,350 --> 00:06:56,480
Do you have any idea?

136
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,810
Let's just walk in openly,

137
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:01,590
find Prince Ying,

138
00:07:01,590 --> 00:07:03,050
and ask him why he didn't sympathize with the people

139
00:07:03,050 --> 00:07:07,250
and even allowed wicked servants to beat the old stronghold chief to death.

140
00:07:07,670 --> 00:07:09,550
That's a good idea.

141
00:07:10,370 --> 00:07:12,090
Go ask him.

142
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:12,610
Okay.

143
00:07:18,650 --> 00:07:19,600
Go.

144
00:07:22,490 --> 00:07:23,930
He won't admit it,

145
00:07:23,930 --> 00:07:24,570
right?

146
00:07:25,270 --> 00:07:25,870
Stupid!

147
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:31,640
Officers, officers!

148
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:34,320
We paid taxes last month.

149
00:07:34,580 --> 00:07:36,100
You had eaten last month.

150
00:07:36,540 --> 00:07:38,230
Don't you need to eat this month?

151
00:07:38,230 --> 00:07:40,100
When you have enough money to pay taxes,

152
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:42,650
come to the government office and exchange these.

153
00:07:42,650 --> 00:07:43,330
Hey, you!

154
00:07:43,330 --> 00:07:44,050
I'm begging you!

155
00:07:44,050 --> 00:07:44,640
We've been looking for you for a while.

156
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:45,650
You haven't paid your vegetable tax yet.

157
00:07:45,650 --> 00:07:46,120
Stop!

158
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:47,650
What kind of a world is this?

159
00:07:49,590 --> 00:07:50,470
Ma'am,

160
00:07:50,710 --> 00:07:52,130
what taxes did those two officers

161
00:07:52,130 --> 00:07:53,210
just collect?

162
00:07:54,590 --> 00:07:55,940
All kinds of taxes.

163
00:07:56,490 --> 00:07:57,680
Bandit suppression tax,

164
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,610
river management tax,

165
00:07:58,610 --> 00:07:59,670
city building tax.

166
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:02,580
Taxes are collected for the Emperor's birthday,

167
00:08:02,580 --> 00:08:03,900
and even

168
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,270
for the Princess's birthday.

169
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:08,750
They are pushing people to their death!

170
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:11,400
You old hag,

171
00:08:11,420 --> 00:08:13,480
what nonsense are you talking about?

172
00:08:15,850 --> 00:08:17,680
I was talking nonsense.

173
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:19,680
-Ma'am...
-I was talking nonsense.

174
00:08:20,410 --> 00:08:21,390
How could they do this?

175
00:08:21,390 --> 00:08:22,670
How dare they do this?

176
00:08:23,620 --> 00:08:25,350
They've always been like this.

177
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:27,760
As you have seen in the last few days,

178
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:28,930
I didn't lie.

179
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,480
You're right.

180
00:08:31,790 --> 00:08:33,700
Let's break into Prince Ying's Mansion tonight.

181
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,559
I'll confront Uncle face to face.

182
00:08:38,510 --> 00:08:40,039
What a great opportunity!

183
00:08:40,330 --> 00:08:42,090
Ma Dayou is seeking his own death.

184
00:08:42,090 --> 00:08:42,850
Wait here.

185
00:08:42,850 --> 00:08:44,159
I'll go and report to Prince Ying.

186
00:08:44,159 --> 00:08:46,370
Tonight, he won't escape.
